**`InjectOsloPolicyConfig` panics when `config` is nil**

When `policyFilePath` is non-empty and `config` is `nil`, the assignment `config["oslo_policy"] = make(map[string]string)` at line 107 panics with `"assignment to entry in nil map"`. Reading from a nil map is safe in Go, but writing to one is not.

Although the typical calling pipeline always passes the non-nil result of `MergeDefaults`, the function has no nil guard and will panic if called directly with a nil map — a realistic scenario in unit tests or future callers that build the config incrementally.

The test suite covers `config: map[string]map[string]string{}` (non-nil empty map) but there is no test for `nil` config with a non-empty `policyFilePath`.

```suggestion
func InjectOsloPolicyConfig(config map[string]map[string]string, policyFilePath string) {
	if policyFilePath == "" || config == nil {
		return
	}
	if config["oslo_policy"] == nil {
		config["oslo_policy"] = make(map[string]string)
	}
	config["oslo_policy"]["policy_file"] = policyFilePath
}
```
